&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What This Role Really Is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our &lt;strong&gt;Social Media Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you’ll own how MeltPlan shows up in public. You’ll create &lt;strong&gt;AI-powered short-form content&lt;/strong&gt; including videos, reels, stories, and experimental formats using modern AI tools instead of traditional production workflows. You’ll engage directly with architects, engineers, and builders, start real conversations, and help build an active community around AI and the future of construction, not just posts and follower counts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for someone who loves being around people and loves creating. Someone who naturally builds relationships, enjoys talking and engaging, and wants to be visibly involved in shaping how an entire industry thinks about AI. You’ll work closely with the founding team to help lead the narrative of AI in construction and define how a new category is understood.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is also a rare opportunity to become &lt;strong&gt;AI-first by default&lt;/strong&gt;. You’ll get hands-on exposure to AI tools across video creation, storytelling, editing, experimentation, and community building. If you want to become the kind of social media marketer who deeply understands AI, not just someone who uses it occasionally, this role is designed for that path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
